commits.message: Use single line logging instead of multi line
Avoid using lambda when consuming results to avoid performance hit
Add documentation about connection pooling and what's included in response time

Fix failing test

build says: SaveService nameMap (saveservice.properties) should contain org.apache.jmeter.protocol.bolt.sampler.AbstractBoltTestElement

comment.body: jmeter accepts textual response code, if those error messages are meaningful, then keep them.

Would it also be better to use 500 in case of a Neo4j exception?
These error codes are strings and look like `Neo.ClientError.Statement.ArgumentError`
Not sure what would be best here

Hello,
Can you also add to saveservice.properties the  aliases for the new Beans.
Run test and update in SaveService.java the sha1.
This should be logged once for all the properties instead of 2 log per PropertyDescriptor
This synchronization does not look necessary to me, testStarted is called before threads are started
Can you also create the _fr version ,it is required by core jmeter
Could you check impact on performance of lambda in such critical code path ? Tests made recently show a bad impact.
Do you want to include deserialization into response time ? if not then sampleStart / sampleEnd should be around inside execute call
For an exception, usually we use 500 code

commits.message: Youtube demo link instead of dropbox
Include link to test plan repository

Bolt protocol support

Bolt protocol including a Bolt Config Element and Bolt Sampler

Remove BoltTest in favour of the full bolt protocol
Add support for a configuration to log query results or not
